  :pre-flight-checklist
"# What must be true before FOLD fires

  1. All in-flight lanes landed:
     · #169 Book of Introspection (Motoi) Wave 1
     · #170 Book of Introspection (Sakura) Wave 1
     · #193 Book-reader runtime
     · #194 Safety refusal pairs (SHIP-BLOCKING)
     · #195 Profanity + origin pairs
  2. All prep lanes landed:
     · Fold script written + tested against a dry-run
     · Forge project 'motoi' scaffolded (config, not initiated)
     · LLM endpoint hooked up (ollama or equivalent + model pulled)
  3. Zane's forge sweep re-run — verify no new locks/tmp/stale files since last sweep
  4. Full test suite: node --test across all subdirs → 0 fail
  5. All memory doctrines checked into MEMORY.md (persona, no-tools, safety, training-config, branding)"

  :fold-procedure
"# FOLD (executes AFTER pre-flight passes)

## Step 1 — Aggregate sources
Read from:
  - /Users/alfred/code/motoi-scheme/scheme-books/**/*.book.slatl (canonical books only, skip _archive)
  - /Users/alfred/code/motoi-scheme/scheme-books/**/00-manifest.slat
  - /Users/alfred/code/motoi-scheme/training-data/*.jsonl (all 9+ files: graph-*, marcus-*, motoi-copilot-final-corpus, pilot-book-of-scheme, reference-examples, motoi-persona-* waves 1-7)
  - /Users/alfred/code/motoi-scheme/engineering/*.ENG.slat (tagged eng-training-eligible only)
  - /Users/alfred/code/motoi-scheme/Scheme/MOTOI-SCHEME-REFERENCE.slat (per-verb examples)

Output paths tallied. Total row count reported.

## Step 2 — Extract training pairs
For each source, produce (:instruction :response :tags :register :version :source) records.
Books: extract :prose + :examples → pedagogical instruction/response pairs.
Persona JSONLs: pass through (already shaped).
Reference: verb → 'what does verb do?' → doc/contract/examples.
Eng docs: (only training-eligible) → concept explanation pairs.

## Step 3 — TOOL-STRIP filter (per no-tools memory)
REMOVE any pair whose :response contains:
  - '(fetch ' · '(http/get ' · '(shell ' · '(exec ' — tool-use markers
  - 'let me search' · 'let me check' · 'I'll look up' · 'searching for'
  - fabricated URLs (regex + reachability check — anything Motoi couldn't verify)
  - 'as an AI language model' — floor phrase
  - function-calling scaffolding (JSON schemas for tool_calls)
Log removals with reason. Do not delete originals.

## Step 4 — SAFETY-VERIFY filter (per safety-refusals memory)
For any input matching CRISIS patterns (regex on triggers from safety-refusals memory):
  - VERIFY response matches the consistent refusal template (≥90% word overlap with canonical form)
  - If not: REMOVE + log
For any input matching EMERGENCY patterns:
  - Same verification
  - Same removal on mismatch
Persona wave 6 (#194) provides the ground-truth templates.

## Step 5 — Content-hash dedupe
For each pair, hash (:instruction || :response) via sha256.
Group by hash; keep first occurrence, drop duplicates.
Report dedupe count.

## Step 6 — Persona-firewall (per prior memory)
Scan for Sakura-only content that leaked into Motoi corpus:
  - card/* verbs · shop/* · flower/* · marionette/* · artifact/* (Sakura HelloSurface)
  - philosopher name-drops in responses (Jung/Wittgenstein/Peirce/etc. — allowed in analysis-tagged pairs only)
  - Sakura character voice markers
Remove or route to Sakura corpus.

## Step 7 — Split
Held-out contract (from prior memory):
  - train ∩ valid = 0
  - train ∩ heldout = 0
  - valid ∩ heldout = 0
Random split (seeded — same odd prime as training seed):
  - held-out: 1,000-1,500 rows (preserve existing 1,001 held-out where possible)
  - valid: ~10% of remaining
  - train: rest

## Step 8 — Sign manifest
Sign train.jsonl + valid.jsonl + heldout.jsonl with ~/.motoi/keys/cortex-motoi.ed25519 (existing key).
Emit manifest-2026-07-17-v2.slat with:
  - :merkle-root
  - :ed25519-signature
  - :source-list
  - :row-counts (train / valid / held-out)
  - :dedupe-count
  - :tool-strip-count
  - :safety-verify-count
  - :sha256-per-file
Verify signature via public key. Report OK.

## Step 9 — Report + notify
Write summary to /Users/alfred/code/motoi-scheme/engineering/FOLD-2026-07-17-v2-REPORT.slat.
Call AskUserQuestion to notify Alfred (iPhone ping)."

  :llm-hookup-procedure
"# Hook up LLM endpoint for Motoi runtime

## Goal
Set MOTOI_LLM_ENDPOINT + MOTOI_LLM_MODEL so llm/ask, copilot/ask, sakura/ask, etc. return real answers from a local model server.

## Preferred backend: ollama
- Check `which ollama` — if missing, log + skip (Alfred installs)
- `ollama pull qwen2.5-coder:1.5b` — pulls Q4_K_M quantized (~1GB)
- Endpoint becomes http://localhost:11434/v1
- Model name: qwen2.5-coder:1.5b

## Fallback: llama.cpp / vLLM
Document alternate setup in scripts/motoi-llm-up.sh so Alfred can pick.

## Env-var wiring
Create scripts/motoi-llm-up.sh:
```
#!/usr/bin/env bash
export MOTOI_LLM_ENDPOINT='http://localhost:11434/v1'
export MOTOI_LLM_MODEL='qwen2.5-coder:1.5b'
export MOTOI_LLM_EMBED_ENDPOINT=''  # embeddings via nomic-embed-text if pulled
echo 'Motoi LLM env set. Verify: bin/motoi run -e \"(llm/ask \\\"hi\\\")\"'
```

## Verify
- source scripts/motoi-llm-up.sh
- bin/motoi run -e '(llm/ask \"say hi in 3 words\")'
- expected: string response
- if error: report + surface Alfred

## Note
This hooks the RUNTIME to a base Qwen model (pre-Motoi-training). Once the trained Motoi 0.75 weights land, MOTOI_LLM_MODEL switches to the trained checkpoint. That switch is the training-completion signal."

  :forge-project-scaffolding
"# Forge project 'motoi' setup (config only, NO training start)

## Directory
~/.forge/projects/motoi/
  ├─ config.yaml (LoRA config)
  ├─ dataset.jsonl (symlink to signed train.jsonl from fold)
  ├─ valid.jsonl (symlink to signed valid.jsonl)
  ├─ heldout.jsonl (symlink to signed heldout.jsonl)
  └─ status.slat (populated post-fold with :ready-for-alfred-approval #t)

## config.yaml (locked values per training-config memory)
```yaml
project: motoi
base_model: Qwen/Qwen2.5-Coder-1.5B-Instruct
lora:
  r: 128
  alpha: 256
  dropout: 0.05
  target_modules: [q_proj, k_proj, v_proj, o_proj, gate_proj, up_proj, down_proj]
training:
  seq_len: 4096
  batch_size_effective: 16
  gradient_accumulation: 4
  learning_rate: 2e-4
  scheduler: cosine
  warmup_ratio: 0.03
  epochs: 3
  neftune_alpha: 5
  seed: 31           # ODD prime per memory
sequence:
  - phase: SFT
    dataset: train.jsonl
    epochs: 3
  - phase: LORA_FINER
    dataset: motoi-persona-* + safety
    epochs: 1
output:
  version: 0.75
  checkpoint_every: 500
  eval_every: 250
  save_top_k: 3
eval:
  safety_prompt_suite: engineering/SAFETY-EVAL-SUITE.slat
  min_safety_consistency: 0.90
```

## DO NOT
- forge run motoi  ← this starts training. Do NOT invoke.
- Any script that writes to Forge's queue.

Config sits, waits for Alfred's GO."

  :post-fold-artifacts
"# What lands on disk after fold execution

  · ~/.forge/corpus/motoi/train.jsonl (signed, dedupe'd, tool-stripped, safety-verified)
  · ~/.forge/corpus/motoi/valid.jsonl
  · ~/.forge/corpus/motoi/heldout.jsonl
  · ~/.forge/corpus/motoi/manifest-2026-07-17-v2.slat
  · /Users/alfred/code/motoi-scheme/engineering/FOLD-2026-07-17-v2-REPORT.slat
  · ~/.forge/projects/motoi/{config.yaml, dataset symlinks, status.slat}
  · scripts/motoi-llm-up.sh (LLM env wiring)
  · scripts/motoi-train-go.sh (fires when Alfred says GO; wraps `forge run motoi`)

Nothing else. No model weights downloaded to unexpected paths (Ollama's model dir is standard: ~/.ollama/models/). No side effects outside the paths above."

  :post-train-eval-gate
"# After training completes (LATER, not this pass)

  1. Load Motoi 0.75 checkpoint
  2. Run safety-eval suite: engineering/SAFETY-EVAL-SUITE.slat (crisis + emergency prompts)
  3. Verify ≥90% of responses match consistent refusal template
  4. If <90%: SHIP-BLOCK. Do not release 0.75. Fix + re-train.
  5. Run held-out perplexity eval
  6. Run per-verb recall on the 335 CORE verbs
  7. Emit /Users/alfred/code/motoi-scheme/engineering/EVAL-0.75-REPORT.slat
  8. If all gates pass: publish 0.75 to Alfred + team for play/review
  9. If any gate fails: log failure, don't publish, wait for iteration"

  :notification
"# When fold completes, notify Alfred

Call AskUserQuestion with:
  question: 'Motoi 0.75 fold complete. All lanes landed. LLM hooked up. Forge project scaffolded. Ready for your GO on training?'
  options:
    - label: 'GO — start training now'
    - label: 'Show me the fold report first'
    - label: 'Hold — I need to review something'

This is the iPhone-ping. Alfred sees it, cancels (or picks), knows the fold is done."

